Nigeria's President, Muhammadu Buhari, who is notorious for embarking on trips around the world, will be jetting out to The Gambia by next week, SaharaReporters has learnt. The advance team of the President would leave by next week, few days after which Buhari would join them in the West African country.  SaharaReporters learnt that Buhari will be attending the country's President's swearing-in ceremony. "There's a trip to Gambia coming up. They are leaving next week. So, Buhari will leave a few days after their departure. He's going to swearing in of Gambian President," a top source told SaharaReporters. Buhari was last in Turkey in December 2021. SaharaReporters had reported at that time that he would also be embarking on local trips to Ebonyi, Kano as well as to his hometown of Daura in Katsina State where he was likely to spend the New Year break.



